<h1>Butter Frosting</h1>

<h3>Ingredients</h3>

<ul>
  <li>2 tablespoons plus 2 teaspoons margarine</li>
  <li>2 ¼ cups sifted powdered sugar</li>
  <li>2 tablespoons milk</li>
  <li>¼ teaspoon vanilla</li>
  <li>Additional milk as needed</li>
</ul>  

<h3>Directions</h3>

<ol>
  <li>In a bowl, beat margarine until fluffy.</li>
  <li>Gradually add 1 cup of the powdered sugar, beating well.</li>
  <li>Slowly beat in the milk and vanilla.</li>
  <li>Slowly beat in remaining sugar.</li>
  <li>Beat in additional milk if needed, to make it a spreading consistency.</li>
  <li>Frost sides and top on single layer round cake for.</li>
</ol>  

<h6>You may substitute the following for variations in the Butter frosting:</h6>

<p><strong>Chocolate Butter frosting:</strong> Prepare as above except beat ¼ cup unsweetened cocoa powder into butter.</p>

<p><strong>Mocha Butter frosting:</strong> Prepare as above except beat ¼ cup cocoa powder into margarine. Add 1 teaspoon instant coffee crystals to the 2 tablespoons of milk. Let in stand for 3 minutes; stir well.</p>
